This is YOUR hardware (the host machine running CloudNode), not
the Command Center's cloud disk.  When it fills, the CloudNode
will stop writing new local recordings — live streaming continues,
but recorded segments stop persisting.

What to do:
  - Free up space on the host (delete old recordings off the
    /var/lib/sourcebox-sentry-cloudnode/ directory, or whichever
    path your install uses).
  - Or: lower the recording retention cap in the per-camera
    recording policy so the node prunes more aggressively.
  - Or: expand the host's storage (mount a larger drive, swap
    the SD card on a Pi, etc.).

You'll get a follow-up email if the disk stays low after 6 hours.
Manage email alerts: {{ dashboard_url }}/settings#settings-notifications
